Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Fan suffers possible heart attack at U-M/MSU game Mark Snyder, Detroit Free Press 9:43 a.m. EDT October 19, 2015 Defocused shot of an ambulance on a city street (Photo: Getty Images) 
An individual was taken to the hospital with a possible heart attack at the conclusion of Saturday's Michigan-Michigan State game. 
Diane Brown, spokesperson for U-M's Division of Public Safety & Security, confirmed that a fan at the game was taken to Michigan's University Hospital in the ER. 
She would no release details of the individual but noted that emergency personnel were not delayed in getting to the person. 
The incident was treated at the end of the game, though it is unknown if it was actually during the final seconds.
